# Plan authoring

When writing or editing plans under `.cursor/plans/`:

**Output locale:** [output-locale.md](../plans/_shared/output-locale.md) — plan body and user replies **English**; code identifiers **English**.

## Required

1. YAML frontmatter with `name`, `overview`, `todos[]`, `isProject: false`
2. **Brief (approved)** section — copy from `.cursor/plans/_briefs/{slug}.brief.md` or inline if brief is embedded
3. **Scope** — in scope / out of scope
4. **Verification** — link [verification.md](../plans/_shared/verification.md); scenarios table if UI

## UI pattern (conditional)

Apply stack-specific UI rules from brief:

| brief.ui_pattern / stack | Required in plan |
|--------------------------|------------------|
| `component-library` | Library name + page/component tree |
| `tailwind-custom` | Token/theme + component list |
| `bootstrap` | Bootstrap layout + component mapping |
| `vanilla-js` | HTML/CSS/JS file tree, no framework sections |
| `native-ui` | Platform UI kit (Material, SwiftUI, etc.) |

Do not force a product-specific UI DSL unless the brief and repo confirm it.

## Plan vs implement

| Mode | Plan file |
|------|-----------|
| Create plan | New or intentional overwrite; English body |
| Implement | Body read-only; only `todos[].status` |
| Close | Optional English status line in `overview` |

## Save paths

```
.cursor/plans/_briefs/{slug}.brief.md     ← intake output
.cursor/plans/features/{slug}.plan.md     ← feature plan
.cursor/plans/design-{slug}.plan.md     ← design-only
```

